<?xml encoding="ISO-8859-1"?>

<tutorial>
    <slide>
        <speech>Hello! My name is Xiao Long - nice to meet you. I will be your guide and assist you in rebuilding your village.</speech>
        <cameraMove>5120,3008</cameraMove>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lockClick></lockClick>
        <lock>
            <villager></villager>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
            <objectiveButton></objectiveButton>
            <timeGroup></timeGroup>
            <scroll></scroll>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
            <buildingButton></buildingButton>
            <popup></popup>
            <buttonOk></buttonOk>
            <buttonCancel></buttonCancel>
            <buttonClose></buttonClose>
            <manpowerSelect></manpowerSelect>
            <lockDropTokens></lockDropTokens>
        </lock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This is your town hall, the heart of the village. The town hall controls how many buildings you can build in your village. You may upgrade your town hall once you have obtained enough resources to unlock more buildings.</speech>
        <fade_out>160</fade_out>
        <highlight>special</highlight>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>0</arrowX>
        <arrowY>0</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Look! Two refugees have just arrived at the city gates.</speech>
        <cameraMove>4400,2500</cameraMove>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lockClick></lockClick>
        <addVillager>2</addVillager>
        <fade_in>0</fade_in>
        <hideArrow></hideArrow>
        <deHighlight></deHighlight>
        <unlock>
            <pause></pause>
        </unlock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>They are most likely villagers displaced by the war. You will have to provide them with food and shelter if you want them to remain in your village.</speech>
        <cameraMove>4800,3168</cameraMove>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lockClick></lockClick>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Luckily, we have an empty home ready. Let us build a road to the home so that the refugees can get to it.</speech>
        <highlight>housing</highlight>
        <fade_out>160</fade_out>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>0</arrowX>
        <arrowY>50</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>To build a road, first tap on the build button.</speech>
        <deHighlight></deHighlight>
        <highlight>buildButton</highlight>
        <unlock>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
        </unlock>
        <lock>
            <teachBuildRoad></teachBuildRoad>
        </lock>
        <fade_out>160</fade_out>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>345</arrowX>
        <arrowY>-265</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>320</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Now, tap on build path.</speech>
        <deHighlight>buildButton</deHighlight>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <lock>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
        </lock>
        <unlock>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
        </unlock>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>65</arrowX>
        <arrowY>20</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Next, tap where you want the road to start. Then tap on where you want the road to end. The road path will be highlighted. Tap again on the end of the road to confirm and build the road.</speech>
        <fade_in>0</fade_in>
        <hideArrow></hideArrow>
        <unlock>
            <scroll></scroll>
        </unlock>
        <showObjective></showObjective>
        <connectHouse></connectHouse>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Great work! Now the refugees will move into their new home. Once they have settled in, they will officially become villagers. You may assign villagers to do various tasks like building and farming.</speech>
        <fade_out>160</fade_out>
        <lock>
            <scroll></scroll>
        </lock>
        <hideObjective></hideObjective>
        <cameraMove>4800,3168</cameraMove>
        <highlight>housing</highlight>
        <lockClick></lockClick>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This is a home. Homes provide shelter for your villagers and are where they go to replenish their energy. Occupied homes also provide you with gold through taxes. Wait for the villagers to find home.</speech>
        <waitForVillager></waitForVillager>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>The refugees appear to have settled in nicely, but now they are hungry! Luckily, we also have a granary ready.</speech>
        <cameraMove>5504,2816</cameraMove>
        <deHighlight></deHighlight>
        <highlight>granary</highlight>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lockClick></lockClick>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This is a granary. Granaries store food and feed your villagers when they are hungry. Link the granary so that your villagers can eat!</speech>
        <fade_in>0</fade_in>
        <deHighlight></deHighlight>
        <unlock>
            <scroll></scroll>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
        </unlock>
        <showObjective></showObjective>
        <connectGranary></connectGranary>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Great! Now your villagers have food and shelter. However, it looks like your food supply is running low. Let us remedy that.</speech>
        <hideObjective></hideObjective>
        <hideArrow></hideArrow>
        <lock>
            <scroll></scroll>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
        </lock>
        <unlock>
            <teachBuildRoad></teachBuildRoad>
        </unlock>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Tap on the build menu again.</speech>
        <showObjective></showObjective>
        <unlock>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
        </unlock>
        <lock>
            <teachBuildFarm></teachBuildFarm>
        </lock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Farm is the place for the villages to produce food through farming activity. These food will be stored in granary or market.</speech>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <contentOffX>400</contentOffX>
        <hideArrow></hideArrow>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lock>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
        </lock>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>845</arrowX>
        <arrowY>20</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This shows the gold cost of the building.</speech>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>790</arrowX>
        <arrowY>125</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This shows the number of workers needed to build the building.</speech>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <arrowX>850</arrowX>
        <arrowY>125</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This is the estimated time to build the building.</speech>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <arrowX>907</arrowX>
        <arrowY>125</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>This shows how many more of this type of building you can build.</speech>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <arrowX>920</arrowX>
        <arrowY>105</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>For now, select the farm and choose a location to build it.</speech>
        <offY>220</offY>
        <lock>
            <scroll></scroll>
        </lock>
        <unlock>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
        </unlock>
        <showArrow></showArrow>
        <arrowX>845</arrowX>
        <arrowY>20</arrowY>
        <arrowAngle>0</arrowAngle>
        <arrowScale>1</arrowScale>
        <arrowLayer>1</arrowLayer>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>When constructing a building, you have to assign villagers to work on it. The left screen shows your available villagers and their happiness and energy levels.</speech>
        <fade_out>160</fade_out>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lock>
            <scroll></scroll>
            <buildButton></buildBUtton>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
        </lock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Working takes energy that can be replenished by sleeping or eating. Happier villagers will work faster.</speech>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>For now, just allocate one villager and tap on the green tick to confirm.</speech>
        <hide></hide>
        <delay>3</delay>
        <unlock>
            <manpowerSelect></manpowerSelect>
            <buttonOk></buttonOk>
        </unlock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Remember to link the location to your village or construction cannot start!</speech>
        <checkFarm></checkFarm>
        <fade_in>0</fade_in>
        <notFirst></notFirst>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Ensure the farm is connected.</speech>
        <connectFarm></connectFarm>
        <unlock>
            <scroll></scroll>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
            <teachBuildFarm></teachBuildFarm>
        </unlock>
        <lock>
            <teachBuildRoad></teachBuildRoad>
        </lock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Wait for the construction of the farm to be finished.</speech>
        <fade_in>0</fade_in>
        <lock>
            <buildButton></buildButton>
            <buildScroll></buildScroll>
            <teachBuildFarm></teachBuildFarm>
        </lock>
        <unlock>
            <scroll></scroll>
            <teachBuildRoad></teachBuildRoad>
        </unlock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Great work! Now we have a farm ready. In order to begin farming, tap on the farm to allocate a villager to work on it.</speech>
        <hideObjective></hideObjective>
        <unlock>
            <manpowerSelect></manpowerSelect>
            <buttonOk></buttonOk>
            <teachBuildFarm></teachBuildFarm>
            <popup></popup>
        </unlock>
        <lock>
            <teachFarming></teachFarming>
        </lock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Farming will begin once you have allocated a villager. Harvested food will be brought to the granary automatically.</speech>
        <lock>
            <popup></popup>
            <scroll></scroll>
        </lock>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>When villagers complete a task, they will gain happiness. Happy villagers will be more likely to drop reputation tokens that will increase your 仁^.</speech>
        <unlock>
            <teachFarming></teachFarming>
            <scroll></scroll>
        </unlock>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>The higher your 仁^, the more renowned your village will become. Certain unlocks become available after a certain amount of ^仁^ is earned.</speech>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Look, villagers are dropping reputation tokens, collect them before they disappear!</speech>
        <triggerDropToken></triggerDropToken>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Look! More refugees have arrived. Let us get to work on expanding the village.</speech>
        <cameraMove>4400,2500</cameraMove>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
        <lockClick></lockClick>
        <addVillager>1</addVillager>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <speech>Try to expand the village to have 8 citizens (villagers have home).</speech>
        <showObjective></showObjective>
        <clickToNext></clickToNext>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <hideBubble></hideBubble>
        <unlockAll><unlockAll>
    </slide>
    <slide>
        <clear></clear>
    </slide>
</tutorial>
